        <link href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nile"/>
        <updated>2026-04-17T07:08:43.801Z</updated>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[... that the <b><a href="/wiki/Nile" title="Nile">Nile</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> is the longest river in the world, but the volume of water it carries is only about 1% of the <a href="/wiki/Amazon_River" title="Amazon River">Amazon</a>, 6% of the <a href="/wiki/Congo_River" title="Congo River">Congo</a>, and 12% of the <a href="/wiki/Yangtze" title="Yangtze">Yangtze</a>?]]></content>
